commitmsg: bump the version number to 1.0 - final release
bump the version number
Merge pull request #2 from mozilla/shut-it-down

shut it down

inhuman ads infrastructure was decommissioned almost a year ago. this change removes all functionality from the addon, presents a description asking the user to uninstall, and adds a README with some context. A similar set of changes will occur on the AMO page once this is uploaded there.
bump version; remove localhost from permissions

Inject a version field into pages, so content can know if the addon is
installed and at what version.

* Add-on no longer does XHR to Inhuman Ads server to post
  screenshots. Instead, redirect browser to a page on the site, which
  takes over and prompts for login as needed.
* Switch 'make test' to use nightly
* Version bump
Fix syntax error in manifest
Further reduce required permissions (remove URLs used only for testing)

Reduce permissions needed to the specific Inhuman Ads / Fx Screenshots
sites (vs "<all urls>")

* add a timestamp when redirecting to avoid caching issues on the main page
* add content script to inhuman{prod,stage}.wpengine.com (our WPEngine servers)
* bump version
